channel.title: Open class files to view the text
channel.description: I got the jar that someone posted and turned it into a rar file. I unzipped it and found class files. Is the anyway i can decompile it to view the text or even decompile the jar?

item.title: Open class files to view the text
item.dc:creator: @darscape darscape
item.description:
@darscape wrote:

Just remember that java decompilers only reverse engineer the code. It is not a guaranteed exact copy as it it has to guess in many cases and the results will not compile without you going in and fixing what is missing. In most cases you can take pre-existing code and find changes within the compiled .class files in order to implement it.

I like to use Notepad++ to compare differences.

item.title: Open class files to view the text
item.dc:creator: @Nemesis1 Nemesis-
item.description:
@Nemesis1 wrote:

roflcopterofl:

I got the old jar from 2001 that someone posted and turned it into a rar file. I unzipped it and found class files. Is the anyway i can decompile it to view the text or even decompile the jar?

JAD - http://www.varaneckas.com/jad

It’s a decompiling application, simply drag the class files into the jad.exe, and they will be decompiled, but i won’t promise that it will work, since i bet the files are deobfuscated.
